			<div class="content" id="post-content-571181">
									

<p>I love the picture for this one, and the idea of an SCP monorail tunnel appeals to me a lot. That said, there are a few things I dislike here.</p>
<p>The first, and the least important, is that we already have a Site-XX utility tunnel SCP.</p>
<p>Second, some of the writing seems a tad heavy handed. Easily fixable.</p>
<p>The main problem I have here, though, is the SCP's effect. By which I mean its lack of an effect of its <em>own</em>. By borrowing random effects from other SCPs, this article simultaneously crosspollinates several articles and detracts from the creativity of the article itself. The end result is, to me, a sub-par article that feels forced, as though the author just wanted to write an SCP for the sake of writing one, with no particular inspiration.<br />
The core <em>noun</em> is good (anomalous monorail tunnel + awesome picture), but the <em>verb</em> of the article (random effects from other SCPs) doesn't seem strong enough to stand on its own.<br />
That last addendum, I think, is a step in the right direction. Perhaps if that aspect were developed further, this concept could grow into a solid SCP.</p>

							</div>

								
