														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-571398">
									

<p>A monorail tunnel? We can be just like Black Mesa!</p>
<p>Anyways, what I think is that this article suffers from a certain lack of description, or even implied description. We are told that the monorail seems to have absorbed the effects (there's a problem here;how does the tunnel know what's anomalous? How do the effects get absorbed when they are so varied in nature? Never mind answering those, they're just nitpicks and are solved by simple suspension of disbelief) but we aren't really shown what happens, besides a few imploding personnel here and there. I'm not asking you to spoil the mystery by spelling everything out, but at least hint at some of the effects that have gone through and mixed with others. For this article, just showing us the output won't do, I think. (It's a fine line, though. Too much in the other direction and the artifact's mechanism is laid bare, exposing it as a mental construction instead of a subject of investigation. )</p>
<p>I seem to have rambled a bit. I think it's the result of typing slowly from a cell phone. Short version: show us some evidence.</p>

